vmips-1.5 was released on 17 November 2014.
User-visible changes in version 1.5 (since version 1.4.1):

@itemize @bullet
@item New features/improvements:

@item VMIPS now includes a basic direct-mapped cache simulation. The cache
isolation and cache swap bits in the CP0 Status register are now
honored.

@item The boot monitor distributed with VMIPS now sets up a dummy @code{argv[0]}
value for the loaded program. Also, it halts by entering an infinite
loop rather than attempting to execute a @samp{break} instruction when
it encounters an unexpected exception.

@item The setup assembly routine distributed with VMIPS has been made
more TLB-friendly. Identity virtual-to-physical mappings for the
first few pages of physical RAM are installed in the TLB at program
start time.

@item When @option{-o excmsg} is on, TLB miss addresses will be printed to
stderr.

@item When @option{-o ttydev=stdout} is specified, simulated program output
will be sent to VMIPS's standard output, even if it is not a tty.

@item The interactor can now disassemble memory. Also, stepping in the
interactor now prints the PC after each step.

@item VMIPS now supports more of the GDB remote serial protocol, in support of
the GDB @command{info threads} and @command{detach} commands. The
debug protocol TCP port is now configurable via the @option{-o
debugport} option. Also, if something halts the program while the
debugger interface is active, VMIPS will tell GDB that the program
exited.

@item Bug fixes:

@item A bug was fixed in the debugger interface where disconnecting from
the debugger socket could cause vmips to enter an infinite loop.

@item The interactor will refuse to dump raw memory words at non-word-aligned
addresses.

@item The CP0 Cause register IP field is now recomputed whenever the
register is read, rather than only when exceptions happen. This
makes polling loops with interrupts disabled work correctly.

@item A bug was fixed in the DECstation-compatible clock device which was
preventing some of its registers from being zeroed properly.

@item Some endianness bugs were fixed in the generic memory-mapped device
code and in the DECstation-compatible serial device.
@end itemize

